Reports of violent protests in the early morning hours were received with unconfirmed information of cars being stoned doing the rounds. Several Middelburg residents on social media said that workers living in Mhluzi notified them that they could not get to work. Sergeant Thabitha Leshilo, Mhluzi police spokesperson, said that there were incidents reported during the early morning hours but that the situation is under control and all is quiet at the moment. The police is monitoring the situation closely.